				Sounds kind of desperate.  Horizons has been in the works for a very long time.  I first heard about it shortly after I started playing EQ, which was just a couple of months after release.
<br />

<br />
The point in that is Horizons has been building up what they want to do and how they are going to do for a long time.  Now that the game is actually released I don't think they are anywhere near meeting those expectations that they have been building up for nearly five years.
<br />

<br />
I think more and more people have found Horizons to be lacking and now they are desperate to keep people with further promises.<br />
