			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				I got the letter too.  I played horizon's for a while and I have some information that might clear it up.
<br />

<br />
First off the aquisition was done by Tulga games.  And as woody mentioned  here: <a href="http://forums.gucomics.com/viewtopic.php?t=4337" target="_blank" class="postlink">http://forums.gucomics.com/viewtopic.php?t=4337</a> the whole deal was kinda shady.  Seems the business manager left Artifact and went and formed his own company.  Short while later, Artifact claims they're getting ready to file for chapter 11 and viola Tulga games sweeps in and rescues them.  After reading some other sources I was pretty much convinced that something shady might be afoot there.  Tulumello, I would say, had a least a bit of a gameplan for this.  However shady or not I have to give him some credit for loving the game "that much".
<br />

<br />
As for the game itself?  I'll say I thought they did a good bit of it right.  Crafting was kinda cool, had a real effect on the world, and,  was used.  A LOT.  Dragons had the potential to be awesome but, like so many games, was half assed because the game got pushed out the door before it was ready.  I never got my dragon matured but those that did said it was freaking sweet.  Supposedly they were even going to implement flying lairs (sort of islands in the sky) for dragon housing.  Spell effects were kinda crap and quests were only so so (nothing really inventive in that dept.)   
<br />

<br />
The events were what made the game so damn fun.  Was in a town one night picking up some new recipies for my dwarven house crafter guy (their system was set up so you could work many tradeskills, not just a couple) and the guy next to me keels over all the sudden.  I turn around and "HOLY @#%$" hella big werewolves were invading the town and 1 of them was inside the bank!  So while my crafting side isn't of much use, I'd worked up my combat side (cleric) enough so that I could rez.  So even though I was only level 11 I was able to rez some folks and we rallied and threw the wolves out of town.  Was really fun!  Only reason I'm not still playing the game is they suffered AC 2 syndrome.  Everyone quit playing.  Hard to be a house builder when nobody's in game to need their house built.  Sad really.  I hope when they go under that they at least make the source public so that I can occasionally play on a public server...<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
			</td></tr>
